We now describe the dynamics of the epidemic with vaccination. For a given Susceptible node (i.e., not having contracted the illness nor vaccinated) we consider several independent exponential clocks with parameter r, one for each edge connecting an Infected node (i.e., potential encounters). It will describe the contact process: if this clock rings, the Susceptible makes a transition to state Infected and remain infectious during an exponential time with mean \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
