				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$1/\gamma $$\end{document}1/γ, whereupon it will not longer infect any node, going to Recovered state. Also for the Susceptible, we consider a non-homogeneous Poisson Process with rate \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
