				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$10^4$$\end{document}104 nodes. We observe that density, related to the mean degree of the four networks, is similar. Nevertheless, there are important differences between the averages of the clustering coefficients.Table 2
